# Hollywood generates its own CI from `gha/**`. The emitted workflows and local
# action scaffolding must be tracked because GitHub reads them straight from the
# repo tree and cannot run a build first. Marking them collapses the diffs in
# review, drops them from language stats, and keeps `git log -p` on `gha/**`,
# which is the only place these files are ever authored.
#
# Regenerate with `npm run generate`; never hand-edit an output.
.github/workflows/*.yml linguist-generated=true -whitespace
.github/actions/**/action.yml linguist-generated=true -whitespace
.github/actions/**/src/** linguist-generated=true -whitespace

# JS action bundles are built in-job by `npm run actions` and stay gitignored.
# The rule is here so that if a bootstrap case ever forces one to be committed,
# it lands collapsed and undiffed rather than as a megabyte of minified noise.
.github/actions/**/dist/** linguist-generated=true -whitespace -diff
